###  http://purl.org/gc/debyeSquaredPerAmuAngstromSquared
<http://purl.org/gc/debyeSquaredPerAmuAngstromSquared> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ;
                                                       rdfs:comment "The unit GAMESS (US) reports IR intensity in: Debye**2/amu-Angstrom**2. Distinct from the km/mol convention used by some other quantum chemistry packages (e.g. Gaussian) - the two are not directly comparable without conversion (1 Debye**2/amu-Angstrom**2 = 42.2561 km/mol)."@en ;
                                                       rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://chemicalsemantics.com/> ;
                                                       rdfs:label "Debye^2/amu-Angstrom^2"@en .


